# Package Usage

Use **Yarn** (`yarn add`, `yarn.lock`). Do not add `package-lock.json` or switch package managers.

## Stack map

| Concern | Package | Rule / location |
|---------|---------|-----------------|
| Framework | `next`, `react` | App Router in `src/app/` |
| Styling | `tailwindcss` v4 | `dark-mode-ui.mdc`, semantic tokens in `globals.css` |
| UI structure | Atomic components | `atomic-components.mdc` — compose atoms/molecules |
| Accessible primitives | `@radix-ui/react-*` | `radix-ui.mdc` — use a Radix primitive whenever one fits |
| Form validation | `zod` | `zod-forms.mdc` |
| Form submission | Server Actions | `server-actions.mdc` — **do not** add a second form-submission rule |
| Auth | `@clerk/nextjs` | `src/proxy.js`, Clerk provider in layout |
| CMS | `@prismicio/*` | `src/prismicio.js`, slices in `src/slices/` |
| Database | `drizzle-orm`, `@neondatabase/serverless` | `src/lib/db.js`, `src/db/schema` |
| Web Analytics | `@vercel/analytics` | `<Analytics />` in `src/app/layout.js` |
| Charts | `recharts` | Radar/profile charts (e.g. completed assessment Leadership Profile) |
| PDF export | `@react-pdf/renderer` | Completed assessment results PDF (`src/lib/assessment-pdf.jsx`) |
| Drag and drop reorder | `@dnd-kit/core`, `@dnd-kit/sortable`, `@dnd-kit/utilities` | Assessment structure builder (domains / attributes / statements) |

## Before adding a dependency

1. Check this map and linked rules — prefer extending the approved stack
2. Do not add a second library for the same job (e.g. `react-hook-form` + Zod actions, MUI + Radix, axios for mutations)
3. Install only the Radix primitives you need (`@radix-ui/react-label`, etc.) — not alternate UI kits
4. Update `.env.example` when a package needs new env vars (`env-example.mdc`)

## Avoid without explicit approval

- Client-side mutation libraries (`axios` POST, `fetch("/api/...")`) — use Server Actions
- Form libraries that bypass Server Actions (`react-hook-form` submit handlers posting to APIs)
- Duplicate validation (manual regex in actions when a Zod schema exists)
- CSS-in-JS or component libraries that replace Tailwind + atomic components
